    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#1007\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">educate</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(v.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>15世纪中期， <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">educaten</span>，“抚养（孩子），训练”，源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">educatus</span>，是 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">educare</span> “抚养，培养”（意大利语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">educare</span>，西班牙语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">educar</span>，法语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">éduquer</span> 也有同源词）的过去分词，是 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">educere</span> “带出，引出”的频率动词或其他相关词，源自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">ex-</span> “出”（参见 <a href=\"/cn/word/ex-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ex- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">ex-</a>）和 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">ducere</span> “引导”，源自 PIE 词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*deuk-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *deuk- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*deuk-</a> “引导”。意为“提供学校教育”的用法首次见于1580年代。相关词： <a href=\"/cn/word/educated\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of Educated \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">Educated</a>； <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">educating</span>。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins><p>根据“世纪词典”的说法， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">educere</i> 指的是“通常涉及身体上的养育或支持，而 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">educare</i> 则更多地涉及思想”，并且，“没有权威证明 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">education</i> 的原始意义是‘发掘或展现思维能力’”。</p>"
    }
  ],
